npm i -D nodemon. --> to download the nodemon package 
npm i -D prettier. --> used to resolve conflicts while mergering and pushing on github
        >>have to create two files 
                1. .prettierrc --> for specifiying the things
                2. .prettierignore --> for file which need to be ignore

npm i mongoose
npm i express dotenv

npm install cookie-parser. --> help to used cookies for the authentication
npm i cros --> help to solve the problem of crss origin

for every project we have to create five middleware 
        1.app.use(cros())
        2.app.use(urlencoded)
        3.app.use(express.json())
        4.app.use(express.static("fileName"))
        5.app.use(cookieParser())

npm install mongoose-aggregate-paginate-v2 --> used to write the aggregration query of mongoDb
        >>>>import mongooseAggregatePaginate from 'mongoose-aggregate-paginate-v2';
        >>  videoSchema.plugin(mongooseAggregatePaginate);    

.gitignore generator --> Create useful .gitignore files for your project

npm i bcrypt --> helps you to hash your password 

npm install jsonwebtoken --> used to genarate and used tokens 
        ->>jwt.io
        has three parts 
                1.Header
                2.Payload
                3.Signature

before hashing the password we have to set some middleware 
        1.prehook --> used to hash the password before saving it in the database
        2.posthook --> used to do some action after saving the data in the database

we can do it while 
        1.saving the data
        2.updating the data
        3.deleting the data             
        4.Validating the data

express-fileupload  npm i express-fileupload  -----> Simple express middleware for uploading files.
upload files using multer  
        -->Multer is a node.js middleware for handling multipart/form-data, which is primarily used for uploading files. It is written on top of busboy for maximum efficiency.
  --> https://cloudinary.com/
        on cloudinary we can upload the files and get the url of the file


npm i cloudinary --> Cloudinary is a cloud-based service that provides an end-to-end image and video management solution, including upload, storage, manipulation, optimization, and delivery.
npm i multer --> Multer is a middleware for handling multipart/form-data, which is primarily used for uploading files.

